Desktop Wallpaper Setting Using Group Policy
Requirement

Active Directory Domain Services installed

Domain Controller running

Domain user created

Wallpaper image file (JPG / PNG)

Shared folder accessible to all users

PART 1: Create Shared Folder for Wallpaper
Step 1: Create Folder

Login to Domain Controller

Create a folder
Example:

C:\Wallpaper

Step 2: Copy Wallpaper Image

Copy wallpaper image into the folder
Example:

C:\Wallpaper\wallpaper.jpg

Step 3: Share Folder

Right-click Wallpaper folder

Click Properties

Go to Sharing tab

Click Advanced Sharing

Check Share this folder

Share Name:

Wallpaper


Click Permissions

Allow Read for:

Everyone


Click OK

Step 4: Set NTFS Permission

Go to Security tab

Click Edit

Add Domain Users

Allow Read & Execute

Click OK

Network Path
\\SERVERNAME\Wallpaper\wallpaper.jpg

PART 2: Create Group Policy Object (GPO)
Step 1: Open Group Policy Management

Open Server Manager

Click Tools

Select Group Policy Management

Step 2: Create New GPO

Right-click your Domain or OU

Click Create a GPO in this domain, and Link it here

GPO Name:

Desktop Wallpaper Policy


Click OK

PART 3: Configure Desktop Wallpaper Policy
Step 1: Edit GPO

Right-click Desktop Wallpaper Policy

Click Edit

Step 2: Navigate Policy Path
User Configuration
→ Policies
→ Administrative Templates
→ Desktop
→ Desktop

Step 3: Configure Desktop Wallpaper

Double-click Desktop Wallpaper

Select Enabled

Wallpaper Name:

\\SERVERNAME\Wallpaper\wallpaper.jpg


Wallpaper Style:

Fill


Click Apply

Click OK

Optional: Prevent User from Changing Wallpaper

Open Prevent changing desktop background

Select Enabled

Click OK

PART 4: Apply Group Policy
Step 1: Update Policy on Client Machine

Login to client machine with domain user

Open Command Prompt

Run:

gpupdate /force

Step 2: Restart or Logoff

Restart or logoff user

Verification

Desktop wallpaper is automatically applied

User cannot change wallpaper (if policy enabled)

Conclusion

Desktop Wallpaper has been successfully set using Group Policy in Active Directory environment.
